child prodigy/ˈprɒd.ɪ.dʒi/
a young child with very great talent and ability in something

processing
making sense of the information your brain receives about the external world

gist
general, overall understanding of something, without the detail

tips
useful pieces of advice about how to do something

@blown away
(informal) very impressed or pleasantly surprised by something

trainable
(US) a word from American English meaning that it can be taught or trained

as well
also; too

composer
a person who writes music

expert
a person with a high level of knowledge or skill relating to a particular subject or activity:

reveal
to make known or show something that is surprising or that was previously secret:

investigate
to examine a crime, problem, statement, etc. carefully, especially to discover the truth:

compose
to produce or create music, poems, or a piece of writing:
to form or make up something:

@in a different way to SB 
ex) Artists seem to be processing the visual world in a different way to non-artists

expect
to think or believe something will happen, or someone will arrive:




